# Cognitive Cockpit - Human-in-the-Loop Interface

```elixir
# Module setup - aliases for convenience
alias Indrajaal.Cockpit.Dashboard
alias Indrajaal.Cockpit.SafetyMonitor
alias Indrajaal.Cockpit.MetricsDashboard
alias Indrajaal.Safety.{Guardian, Envelope, DeadMansSwitch}
```

## Overview

The **Cognitive Cockpit** provides a Human-in-the-Loop (HITL) interface for monitoring and controlling the Indrajaal Cortex system.

### STAMP Constraints

| Constraint | Description |
|------------|-------------|
| SC-HITL-001 | Human oversight of autonomic decisions |
| SC-HITL-002 | Continuous safety visibility |
| SC-HITL-003 | Operational metrics dashboard |

---

## Safety Monitor

Real-time visualization of the Safety Envelope and Guardian status.

```elixir
# Safety Score - Overall system safety (0-100)
safety_score = SafetyMonitor.safety_score()

Kino.Markdown.new("""
## Safety Score: #{safety_score}/100

#{cond do
  safety_score >= 90 -> "Status: **HEALTHY** - System operating within safe parameters"
  safety_score >= 70 -> "Status: **WARNING** - Some safety concerns detected"
  safety_score >= 50 -> "Status: **CAUTION** - Multiple safety issues require attention"
  true -> "Status: **CRITICAL** - Immediate intervention required"
end}
""")
```

### Guardian Status

```elixir
guardian_data = SafetyMonitor.guardian_status_data()

Kino.DataTable.new([guardian_data])
```

### Dead Man's Switch

```elixir
dms_data = SafetyMonitor.dms_heartbeat_data()

Kino.Markdown.new("""
### Dead Man's Switch Status

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| State | #{dms_data.state_display} |
| Heartbeats Received | #{dms_data.heartbeats} |
| Heartbeats Missed | #{dms_data.missed} |
| Failsafe Triggers | #{dms_data.failsafes} |
| Current Sequence | #{dms_data.current_sequence} |
| Last Heartbeat | #{dms_data.last_heartbeat} |
""")
```

### Safety Alerts

```elixir
alerts = SafetyMonitor.safety_alerts()

if Enum.empty?(alerts) do
  Kino.Markdown.new("**No active safety alerts**")
else
  alert_rows = Enum.map(alerts, fn alert ->
    level_emoji = case alert.level do
      :critical -> "🚨"
      :warning -> "⚠️"
      :info -> "ℹ️"
      _ -> "❓"
    end
    "| #{level_emoji} #{alert.level} | #{alert.component} | #{alert.message} | #{alert.action} |"
  end)

  Kino.Markdown.new("""
  ### Active Alerts

  | Level | Component | Message | Action |
  |-------|-----------|---------|--------|
  #{Enum.join(alert_rows, "\n")}
  """)
end
```

