## Safety Envelope Visualization

```elixir
# Envelope constraints vs current usage
envelope_data = Dashboard.envelope_data_for_kino()

Kino.Markdown.new("""
### Resource Constraints

| Resource | Current | Maximum | Status |
|----------|---------|---------|--------|
| FLAME Nodes | #{envelope_data.resource.flame_nodes.current} | #{envelope_data.resource.flame_nodes.max} | #{if envelope_data.resource.flame_nodes.current <= envelope_data.resource.flame_nodes.max, do: "OK", else: "VIOLATION"} |
| RAM (MB) | #{envelope_data.resource.ram_mb.current} | #{envelope_data.resource.ram_mb.max} | #{if envelope_data.resource.ram_mb.current <= envelope_data.resource.ram_mb.max, do: "OK", else: "VIOLATION"} |
| CPU % | #{envelope_data.resource.cpu_percent.current} | #{envelope_data.resource.cpu_percent.max} | #{if envelope_data.resource.cpu_percent.current <= envelope_data.resource.cpu_percent.max, do: "OK", else: "VIOLATION"} |

### Temporal Constraints

| Metric | Target | Current |
|--------|--------|---------|
| Response Time (ms) | ≤ #{envelope_data.temporal.response_time_ms.max} | - |
| Heartbeat Interval (ms) | #{envelope_data.temporal.heartbeat_interval_ms.target} | #{envelope_data.temporal.heartbeat_interval_ms.current || "N/A"} |
""")
```

