## System Metrics Dashboard

```elixir
beam = MetricsDashboard.beam_metrics()

Kino.Markdown.new("""
### BEAM VM Metrics

**Memory Usage (MB)**

| Category | Size |
|----------|------|
| Total | #{beam.memory.total_mb} |
| Processes | #{beam.memory.processes_mb} |
| Binary | #{beam.memory.binary_mb} |
| ETS | #{beam.memory.ets_mb} |
| Code | #{beam.memory.code_mb} |
| Atom | #{beam.memory.atom_mb} |

**Runtime**

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Processes | #{beam.processes.count} / #{beam.processes.limit} |
| Schedulers | #{beam.schedulers.online} online |
| Run Queue | #{beam.run_queue} |
| Uptime | #{div(beam.uptime_ms, 1000)} seconds |
""")
```

### Agent Status

```elixir
agents = MetricsDashboard.agent_metrics()

agent_rows = [
  {"Cortex", agents.cortex},
  {"Synapse", agents.synapse},
  {"GDE", agents.gde},
  {"Zenoh", agents.zenoh}
]
|> Enum.map(fn {name, status} ->
  available = Map.get(status, :available, false)
  if available do
    "| #{name} | Available | #{inspect(Map.drop(status, [:available]))} |"
  else
    "| #{name} | Not Available | - |"
  end
end)

Kino.Markdown.new("""
### Cortex Agents

| Agent | Status | Details |
|-------|--------|---------|
#{Enum.join(agent_rows, "\n")}
""")
```

